# Styling Conventions

## Scoped Styles

- Always use `<style scoped>` in Vue components
- Use BEM-like naming for CSS classes (e.g., `.header__container`, `.experience__card`)

## Design Tokens

Prefer Nuxt UI CSS custom properties over raw color values:

```css
/* Use tokens */
background: var(--ui-bg-elevated);
border-color: var(--ui-border);
color: var(--ui-text-muted);

/* Don't hardcode colors */
background: #1a1a1a;
```

## Theme

- Primary color: `emerald` (configured in `app/app.config.ts`)
- Neutral color: `zinc`
- Dark mode is supported via `useColorMode()`

## Tailwind + Scoped CSS

- Use Tailwind utility classes for layout and spacing in templates
- Use scoped `<style>` blocks for component-specific or complex styles
- Keep styles co-located with the component that uses them
